
brief:      "Halden — a single-origin coffee roastery in Bergen that roasts one lot at a time and names the farm on every bag. A cinematic scroll story about the journey from a hillside in Huila to the cup: the altitude, the hands that pick it, the roast curve, the pour. Mood: premium, calm, cinematic."
reasoning:  claude-sonnet-5   (questions · concept · plan · art-direction)
bulk:       claude-sonnet-5   (section codegen · self-critique; escalates to reasoning on repair)
design:     claude-haiku-4-5-20251001   (legacy/fallback tier)

[1m── PLAN ────────────────────────────────────────────────────[0m
brand:  Halden
mood:   premium, calm
layout: origin-to-proof, editorial-brand-story
sections:
  0. masthead         [36mcinematic[0m/xl  Establish Halden's name and the single premise: one lot, one farm, named on every bag
  1. the-altitude     [36meditorial[0m/lg  Ground the origin story in place — the specific farm, elevation, and family behind this lot
  2. the-hands        [36mnarrative[0m/lg  Show the labor of the harvest — picking, sorting, washing — as the source of quality, not an abstraction
  3. the-crossing     [36masymmetric[0m/md  Mark the transition from farm to Bergen roastery — distance, care in transit, the lot arriving intact
  4. the-roast-curve  [36mimmersive[0m/xl  Reveal the craft of roasting this specific lot — the curve, the listening, the judgment call at first crack
  5. the-pour         [36mcinematic[0m/lg  Land in Bergen — the finished cup, the ritual of pouring, the moment the origin becomes taste
  6. the-proof        [36meditorial[0m/md  Close on evidence — this bag, this farm name, this lot number — inviting the reader to hold the origin in hand

